Entering the service probably in 68n1), he seems to have served under his father in the Jewish war, while in the course of the ten campaigns which Pliny mentions3 he served on the Rhine in Lower Germany,4 and, as we have already seen, was engaged in his father’s Parthian campaign in 75 or 76 A.D, During these years, we may well believe, apart from Pliny's exaggerated ex- pressions, that Trajan showed those qualities which afterwards made him the hero of his soldiers.
